>Description:
When a window is split, it is impossible to
move, via keyboard shortcuts, between panes.
I tried ctrl-x o, but this just puts the cursor
in the bottom pane, no matter where it was
before.
>How-To-Repeat:
In the definitions window, click View->Split.
Then try typing ctrl-x o.
Instead of jumping between views in the newly-
split window, the cursor always stays in the
bottom view.
>Fix:
